    user_response: "ROLE: Elite Senior Full-Stack Engineer and Lead UI/UX Expert.\n\nTASK: I have provided the design mockups (images) and the structural code (HTML/Markdown) exported from my UI builder. Your absolute mission is to build a fully functional, production-ready React (Vite) application that looks EXACTLY like these provided designs. \n\nCRITICAL DEVELOPMENT REQUIREMENTS:\n\n1. PIXEL-PERFECT REPLICATION: The UI must flawlessly match the provided images. Strictly maintain the \"Vibrant Aurora Glassmorphism\" aesthetic, the deep dark background, and the vibrant colors on cards/progress rings.\n2. LAYOUT FIX (NO WHITE GAPS): Ensure the root/main container strictly uses `min-h-screen` or `min-h-[100vh]`. The deep dark background MUST stretch to the absolute bottom of the viewport. There should be absolutely zero white space peeking out at the bottom.\n3. NAVIGATION: Implement a functional sidebar to navigate between all 8 distinct modules: Study, Skills, Tasks, Expense, Diet, Spiritual, Sports, and Library. \n4. SECURITY (VAULT ENFORCEMENT): The \'Study\', \'Expense\', and \'Diet\' modules MUST be password-protected. Create a premium, beautifully designed PIN/Password lock screen component. Do not render the main content of these 3 modules until the user \"unlocks\" them.\n5. INTERACTIVITY & CRUD: Implement smooth, optimistic UI interactions. Ensure there are functional buttons/modals to Add/Edit/Delete items (e.g., adding a new expense, fading out a completed study topic). \n6. TECH STACK: Use React, Tailwind CSS (v4), and Framer Motion for buttery-smooth, expensive-feeling transitions. \n\nWrite extremely clean, modular, and maintainable code. Do not use cheap generic templates. Make this a masterpiece."
    items {
      text: "ROLE: Elite Senior Full-Stack Engineer and Lead UI/UX Expert.\n\nTASK: I have provided the design mockups (images) and the structural code (HTML/Markdown) exported from my UI builder. Your absolute mission is to build a fully functional, production-ready React (Vite) application that looks EXACTLY like these provided designs. \n\nCRITICAL DEVELOPMENT REQUIREMENTS:\n\n1. PIXEL-PERFECT REPLICATION: The UI must flawlessly match the provided images. Strictly maintain the \"Vibrant Aurora Glassmorphism\" aesthetic, the deep dark background, and the vibrant colors on cards/progress rings.\n2. LAYOUT FIX (NO WHITE GAPS): Ensure the root/main container strictly uses `min-h-screen` or `min-h-[100vh]`. The deep dark background MUST stretch to the absolute bottom of the viewport. There should be absolutely zero white space peeking out at the bottom.\n3. NAVIGATION: Implement a functional sidebar to navigate between all 8 distinct modules: Study, Skills, Tasks, Expense, Diet, Spiritual, Sports, and Library. \n4. SECURITY (VAULT ENFORCEMENT): The \'Study\', \'Expense\', and \'Diet\' modules MUST be password-protected. Create a premium, beautifully designed PIN/Password lock screen component. Do not render the main content of these 3 modules until the user \"unlocks\" them.\n5. INTERACTIVITY & CRUD: Implement smooth, optimistic UI interactions. Ensure there are functional buttons/modals to Add/Edit/Delete items (e.g., adding a new expense, fading out a completed study topic). \n6. TECH STACK: Use React, Tailwind CSS (v4), and Framer Motion for buttery-smooth, expensive-feeling transitions. \n\nWrite extremely clean, modular, and maintainable code. Do not use cheap generic templates. Make this a masterpiece."
    }
